      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "AFAIK, post shell startup, `_` stores the last argument of the last executed command. E.g. it stores `-G` after the `ls -G` command is executed, `~/Downloads` if `ls -G ~/Downloads` was executed, etc.\r\n\r\nSo in the case above, it should store the pathname `/outdir-base`, i.e. the argument of the last command executed before this line (`cd /outdir-base`). \r\n\r\nUnless I am missing something here.",
      "commit_id" : "2dabd97f95bec3041b82c21132ce07d76fd1ccca",
      "created_at" : "2021-08-07T07:47:38Z",
      "diff_hunk" : "@@ -452,11 +452,7 @@ mv --no-target-directory \"$OUTDIR\" \"$ACTUAL_OUTDIR\" \\\n \n (\n     cd /outdir-base\n-    {\n-        echo \"$GIT_ARCHIVE\"\n-        find \"$ACTUAL_OUTDIR\" -type f\n-    } | xargs realpath --relative-base=\"$PWD\" \\\n-      | xargs sha256sum \\\n+    find \"$GIT_ARCHIVE\" \"$ACTUAL_OUTDIR\" -type f -execdir bash -c 'basename \"$1\" | xargs sha256sum' _ {} \\; \\",
